         <description>Avis Baker-White was born in Baton Rouge, La. She graduated from McKinley
            High School in 1943 at age fifteen, then attended Southern University. She taught at
            McKinley High School for many years, retiring in 1979. She married Gilbert White, a
            pharmacist, and they had three children.</description>
      </name>
